---
title: Sweet & Spicy Avocado Toast with Feta plus Red Pepper Jam, Cucumbers & Crispy Fried Onions
description: Here’s a go-to vegetarian lunch idea we couldn’t wait to tell you about. We start with our beloved avocado toast, but up the ante with chewy ciabatta bread as the base. Add crunchy sliced cucumber, sweet red pepper jam, salty feta, fresh dill, and a naughty little topper of crispy fried onions for a harmonious balance of color, texture, and flavor. And for you hotheads out there, sprinkle away with the chili flakes!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-spicy-avocado-toast-with-feta-9c3fa83f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-spicy-avocado-toast-with-feta-63ec057aa1dd47e2940de34a-3fe5d307.pdf
time required: 10 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 10 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1370 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-spicy-avocado-toast-with-feta-63ec057aa1dd47e2940de34a
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
---

Halve @ciabatta bread{2} and toast in a #toaster{} until golden brown.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @mini cucumber{1}(sliced on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces). Drizzle
with @olive oil{1%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pick and roughly chop
fronds from @dill{1/4%oz}(chopped).

Spread cut sides of ciabattas evenly with @guacamole{1/2%cup}. Top with
cucumber and drizzle with @red pepper jam{1}. Sprinkle with @feta cheese{1/2%cup},
dill, @crispy fried onions{1}, and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like.

Divide toasts between #plates{} and serve.

> For extra heat, adjust the amount of chili flakes to your preference.